### Git Best Practices

#### Git Pager Configuration (Recommended)
Set up git to never use pager for better automation:

```bash
# One-time global setup (recommended)
git config --global core.pager cat

# Alternative: disable pager for specific commands
git config --global pager.diff false
git config --global pager.log false
git config --global pager.show false
```

#### Git Usage Tips
- **After pager setup, all git commands work without manual scrolling**
- **Terminate hanging commands** with Ctrl+C immediately
- **Document hanging commands** in PWSH_ISSUES.md for future reference
- **Test git commands** before using them in scripts

#### Manual Pager Control (if needed)
```bash
# If you ever need pager, use --no-pager explicitly
git --no-pager log --oneline -10
git --no-pager show --name-only HEAD
git --no-pager diff
```

